on life business sport Visual Podcasts SPH Rewards\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 98}, {\"ngram\": \"Paid press releases\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 132}, {\"ngram\": \"Advertise\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest sports news\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 206}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 220}, {\"ngram\": \"Published\\u00c2May\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 234}, {\"ngram\": \"Updated\\u00c2May\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"05:27 AM\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 284}, {\"ngram\": \"NEW YORK\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A tear-jerking corporate advertising campaign from Procter &amp; Gamble saluting the mothers of athletes.\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 467, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A tear-jerking corporate advertising campaign\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"Procter\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 420}, {\"ngram\": \"amp\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 425}, {\"ngram\": \"Gamble\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"the mothers\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The consumer products maker, one of the world's biggest ad spenders and a sponsor of the Olympics, is instead focusing its marketing at the Games on its individual brands including Pampers diapers, Gillette razors and Ariel detergent.\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pampers\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampers\"}, {\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariel_Motorcycles\", \"score\": 0.9991319338898529, \"rank\": 0.0007593261456309559, \"text\": \"Ariel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariel_Motorcycles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariel_Motorcycles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The consumer products maker\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest ad spenders\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"a sponsor\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"its marketing\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"its individual brands\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"Gillette razors\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The move is a step-change for P&amp;G, whose prior Olympics advertising campaigns emphasized the values of the Cincinnati-based company, struck an emotional chord and were among the company's most successful by sales and views, according to the website of Wieden+Kennedy, the agency that worked on the commercials.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The move\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 713}, {\"ngram\": \"a step-change\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"P&amp;G\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 742}, {\"ngram\": \"whose prior Olympics advertising campaigns\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"the Cincinnati-based company\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"an emotional chord\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 867}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"sales\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 921}, {\"ngram\": \"views\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 931}, {\"ngram\": \"the website\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"Wieden+Kennedy\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"the commercials\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the past, we have had both a P&amp;G and a brand focus, and this time we just really decided we are going to go focus, not 100%, but much more prominently, on brands,\\\" said P&amp;G chief brand officer Marc Pritchard.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"a brand focus\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"not 100%\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1152}, {\"ngram\": \"brands\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"P&amp;G chief brand officer Marc Pritchard\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what consumers that we serve are familiar with.\\\"\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"consumers\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Procter &amp; Gamble has reduced its spending on Olympics advertising in the United States by 50% over the last several Games, after previously spending tens of millions of dollars with U.S. broadcaster NBCUniversal, Reuters reported last month.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997310779671832, \"rank\": 0.0002689943681976008, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.999999989114258, \"rank\": 1.0871175003646346e-08, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1517, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999767617285, \"rank\": 2.3238225984703838e-08, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Procter\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"amp\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"Gamble\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"its spending\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1345}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics advertising\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"50%\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1397}, {\"ngram\": \"the last several Games\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"tens of millions\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"dollars\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company is one of the biggest global marketers of consumer products by revenue, selling roughly $82 billion worth in its fiscal year ending June 30, 2023.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The company\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest global marketers\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"consumer products\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1618}, {\"ngram\": \"revenue\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1629}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly $82 billion worth\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"its fiscal year\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It spends about $8 billion annually on advertising.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"advertising\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1757}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pritchard said that for the upcoming Games, P&amp;G is launching advertising for more than 30 of its brands, more than ever before.\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pritchard\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"the upcoming Games\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1802}, {\"ngram\": \"P&amp;G\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"advertising\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"its brands\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1867}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our message really is serving the Olympic and Paralympic athletes, their families and fans around the world,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 2012, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our message\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1905}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic and Paralympic athletes\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a bit of an everyday focus on it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2028}, {\"ngram\": \"an everyday focus\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, P&amp;G marketing at European retailers will emphasize the idea that its products are \\\"everyday champions\\\" in household tasks, according to the company.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"marketing\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2089}, {\"ngram\": \"European retailers\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2111}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2135}, {\"ngram\": \"its products\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2153}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"everyday champions\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"household tasks\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company's biggest marketing push is in Europe because it is the host region for the Games, Pritchard said.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2335, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The company's biggest marketing push\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"the host region\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2318}, {\"ngram\": \"Pritchard\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sponsors of the International Olympic Committee (IOC), including P&amp;G, pay upwards of an estimated $100 million for the right to use the famous Olympic rings in their marketing materials, according to the Reuters report.\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2353, \"end\": 2390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2545, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999767617285, \"rank\": 2.3238225984703838e-08, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sponsors\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"P&amp;G\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2465}, {\"ngram\": \"the famous Olympic rings\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"their marketing materials\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2526}]}, {\"sentence\": \"P&amp;G launched its first ever corporate advertising campaign highlighting the company rather than the household products it makes for the 2010 Vancouver Olympics, according to Wieden+Kennedy.\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2702, \"end\": 2725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998617568, \"rank\": 1.3773770131634033e-10, \"text\": \"2010 Vancouver Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Wi